p understanding of the developer and partner community, identify and fill product gaps and generate new ideas that grow market share, improve customer experience and drive growth. Work closely with engineering teams to deliver with quick time-to-market and optimal resources. Answering specific tech questions on the API in our community forums, at events and via email. This position is completely remote and does not require presence in the office. However, if you are in the Detroit area, and you'd like some company, you are welcome to work from our offices located in Birmingham, MI. Experience as a developer is a must Requirements: Minimum 3 years experience in writing technical documentation describing the API systems and their architecture Strong technical background, especially in APIs with multiple endpoints Analysis and structuring of the existing documentation. Writing documentation style guide and documentation templates. Writing technical documentation for existing functionality. Harmonization of the documentation package with the team. Interaction with product developers, and product teams Knowledge of approaches to documentation (technical writing fundamentals - the target audience, the document structure, document formats, etc.). Thrives in a fast-paced environment where being self-directed, determined, and resilient are a requirement Passion for decentralized and open-source technologies and advocating them to others Bonus Points if you... Have experience in a fast-paced, remote startup environment Skills API, Communications, Technical Writing, Software Development Compensation Negotiable Applications for this job are currently closed. ", 
